  <a href="#0" id="0">
   Robust citation classification has been hindered by the relative lack of annotated data.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   In this paper we successfully use a large, out-of-domain, annotated corpus to improve the citation polarity classification.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Our approach uses a deep learning neural network for domain adaptation with labeled out-of-domain data and unlabeled in-domain data.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   This semi-supervised domain adaptation approach outperforms the in-domain citation polarity classification and other fully supervised domain adaptation approaches.
  </a>
